questions.question_text:
A company wants to automate the orders processed on its website using API. The network device that supports the solution must:

• support XML encoding
• support distributed transactions
• support YANG data models
• be support software redundancy

Which requirement prevents the use of RESTCONF for the solution?

discussion.content:
Selected Answer: C
"Therefore, RESTCONF does not provide for distributed transactions, but only device-by-device configuration."

https://www.claise.be/netconf-versus-restconf-capabilitity-comparisons-for-data-model-driven-management-2/

Answer: D RESTCONF is a protocol that provides a programmatic interface for accessing and manipulating resources defined in the YANG data model. It uses the HTTP protocol for communication and supports JSON encoding for data exchange. However, it does not support XML encoding, which is one of the requirements listed.

comments.content:
The REST-API supports only json. 
RESTCONF supports xml and json.

https://developer.cisco.com/docs/cisco-netconf-and-rest-device-management-api-documentation/#!cisco-netconf-and-rest-device-management-api-documentation/cisco-netconf-and-rest-device-management-api-documentation
So, answer is C.
